go to south karana and join the treant group if u want cash or go join a spire group outside splitpaw if u dont want bad faction with druids P<br>
lvl 29 to 34<br>
stay in sk and solo tesch mas gnolls all the way till 34, these guys will occasionally drop a gnoll hide lariat which u should keep for your pet the stun proc will really help at later lvls. if u think the xp is too slow try going inside paw and join the safe room group just dont pull the caster gnolls behind the double doors.<br>
lvl 34 to 39 (bad faction)<br>
go to the barbarian village in west karana and solo ulrich or get another caster partner and alternate between ulrich and einhorst who spawns in the hut near the river. Warning this should only be done at around lvl 37 or else u will need 1 more person.<br>
lvl 39 to 44 (bad faction)<br>
stay in wk and solo einhorst<br>
lvl 34 to 46+ (good faction)<br>
go to the corrupt guard tower beside the barb village and hunt guard donlan and mccluskey. at 34 u will need to be in a group of 3 or 4, at 39 u will need a partner and at 44 just solo both. these guys drop guard bracers which u should give to the captain at the top of the stone bridge in north karana. at 44 i think, both guards wont give anymore xp but doing the guard bracer quest still will. when i say 46+, it all depends on your patience some ppl can reach 50 just by doing this quest.<br>
lvl 49+<br>
solo seafuries in OOT i think until they stop giving xp or just go on plane raids ) theres a chance where u might get the awesome apothic armour and elemental staff of masterery earth <br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> Perilbane</span><br> <span class=usertitle>Unregistered User</span><br>   <font color=#333333>(7/20/00 1:03:04 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerlibrarysubmissions.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=7.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Corrupt guards in WK</span><hr size=1> I can solo Donlan and McCluskey at 40. Donlan is green at 40 and McCluskey is blue and MUCH harder than Donlan. An Earth pet just stands there and gets the crap pounded out of him by McCluskey. I started using a water pet and rarely lose a pet now. I also have JBoots in case I *do* lose the pet and gotta run around a bit. Any mage that doesn't have JBoots ought to make it a priority.<br>
<br>
Perilbane Mooncaster<br>
MAge of the 40th Circle <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> Perilbane</span><br> <span class=usertitle>Unregistered User</span><br>   <font color=#333333>(7/28/00 3:32:29 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerlibrarysubmissions.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=7.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Update on Donlan and McCluskey</span><hr size=1> Donlan and McCluskey are the corrupt guards in the tower in WK near the Barbarian village. I can solo them but for a long time I needed help breaking the spawn. I was told that a level 40 mage can't break the spawn because we have no snare or mez or whatever. If both guards are up wehn you get there and you try to pull one you're going to get them both. Well being told I CAN'T do something kinda piqued my interest. I've been successful breaking teh spawn now like 3 or 4 times. It's a pain but you can do it with JBoots. Here's how:<br>
<br>
Med full, water pet up and armed, Burnout pet, and flameshield him. Med full is important. Target Donlan (he stands closest to the door while McCluskey spawns more towards the rear of the chamber). Back off really far while keeping Donlan LoS. Fire a Cinder Bolt at Donlan at the MAX range of Cinder bolt. Fire one more as he's running at you and then tell pet to attack. Your pet is gonna die. If both guards are on him hit Donlan with a Blaze. If either guard is running at you, take off EAST so you have a lot of room to run. (I run along the water cause I know where the zone line to NK is.) Donlan should die but if not then it's only gonna take one Blaze to kill him. Run for about 20 RL seconds then stop and hit Blaze. It SHOULD say &quot;Target out of range...&quot; so keep hitting it till it goes off. It will land as the guard gets to within mellee range so be ready to run again INSTANTLY. Finish Donlan if necessary then run McCluskey really far... head back towards Donlan so you can loot him (yeah I'm greedy). Loot and run... McCluskey will kill you and you are petless. Run all the way back to Barbarian village. You should now have time to either cast another pet or med just a little... watch for that guard. Using the entire length of this zone you can kill both guards. Yes, I discovered precisely how pathetic I am at kiting. Because we can't slow them down we have to run them for awful distances. You have to run really long with JBoots to get enough distance to get a cast off. 20 to 25 seconds RL time to get out of range. I don't even bother to turn around to face them... just hammer Blaze till it goes off. Then run again right away. You practically have to run the guards from one end of the zone to the other to have enough time to recast a pet. It's a nasty, lengthy, clunky process, but next time someone says a level 40 Mage can't break this spawn, I'll show them it CAN be done. It just ain't pretty. Oh... this usually has the added benefit of spacing out the guard spawn nicely so you can med up to kill Donlan (this is why I kill him FIRST) cause he's pretty easy to kill. Now you should have time to med to full for McCluskey. (You'll need it. He's tough)<br>
<br>
Perilbane Mooncaster<br>
Mage of the 40th Circle<br>
<br>
