<br>
1.  If you are patient just sit at the tower and every so often McClusky will take a walk.  He is gone for about 5 minutes and then will return.  When he leaves wait a bit and kill Donolan.<br>
<br>
2.  If you are not patient just bribe a druid to harmonize them for you and you are all set.<br>
<br>
Ogron Fionn<br>
52 Elementalist <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uezno.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ezno</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/posticons/eyes.gif BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Master Summoner</span><br>  Posts: 166<br> <font color=#333333>(9/20/00 10:05:40 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerlibrarysubmissions.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=7.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Corrupt Guards</span><hr size=1> <br>
Turning around to face somethign while kiting is just novice.  THE way to kite is to have a quick casting spell up.  As you run continue to hit this spell until it finally says you are Out of Range.  Then stop, count to 1 (sometimes you aren't truely stopped) and then keep hitting your DD until the Mob runs into range.  As soon as the MoB is hit you begin running again.  Start with Blaze as your main DD but some MoBs are fast enough to run up to you before this spell gets off -- if so just repeat using the 176 dmg Shock spell.  <br>
<br>
Using a quick casting spell to figure out when you have gone past the maximum DD range will minimize the time it takes to kite something.   <br>
<br>
---<br>
<br>
Another nice feature of Kiting...  (Not sure how well this works without a snared target because I've never tried it and don't usually need it these days)... killing something even when you run out of mana.   If you run out of mana and still need a blast or two to kill something you can try this: You will need to have some damage done to you to time it right.   Pull up your inventory screen and wait until you see your HP go up. Immediately start counting and when you hit 5 sit down.  When you see your mana bar go up stand up, run and count to 5 again.   I've been able to meditate a full bubble of mana with my druid using this method.  With a magician you might have to count to 11 (skip a tick) to make sure you have enough distance to do this.   <p> <br>
